{"id":"ev_c1541c74c1f84595","runId":"run_205","type":"delegation","at":1782235271914,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_45138b870d0944a8","atom":0,"task":"Fix ticket 0041: the authoring-Play in-flight guard in packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts (requestAuthoringPlay, ~L1372) is the outlier among post-wrap daemon ops. It currently does `if (ctx.inFlight.size > 0)` — a GLOBAL, status-blind refusal that blocks authoring whenever ANY run on ANY workspace is in flight, including the same wrapped (awaiting-founder) run on this workspace. Its siblings scope to the workspace and only refuse a still-running run: requestSupportCommitRun (~L871-873) uses `ctx.inFlight.get(run.workspaceId)` and refuses on `run.status === 'running' || (inFlightRunId && inFlightRunId !== runId)`; requestOscarDebRepair (~L946-952) refuses on `sourceRun?.status === 'running' || (activeRunId && activeRunId !== input.sourceRunId)`.\n\nWHAT TO CHANGE — in requestAuthoringPlay only, replace the `if (ctx.inFlight.size > 0)` block with a workspace-scoped, status-aware guard. AuthoringPlayInput has NO runId field (it is workspace-scoped) and inFlight is Map<workspaceId, runId|'pending'> with at most one entry per workspace, so the precise condition is: look up the workspace's in-flight entry and refuse ONLY if it represents a still-active run — i.e. the entry is the 'pending' mid-launch reservation OR resolves to a run whose status === 'running'. Allow when the in-flight entry resolves to a wrapped run (status !== 'running', e.g. awaiting-founder) — that is the SAME run the founder is authoring from post-wrap, exactly the case support-commit and Deb-repair already permit. Concretely:\n\n  const activeRunId = ctx.inFlight.get(input.workspaceId)\n  const activeRun = activeRunId ? ctx.store.getRun(activeRunId) : null\n  if (activeRunId && (!activeRun || activeRun.status === 'running')) {\n    return { status: 409, body: { error: 'refusing to run authoring Play: a run is still active on this workspace (would orphan it) — wait for it to wrap or finish' } }\n  }\n\nKeep the 409 status. Add a brief comment at the guard stating the chosen condition and WHY it matches its siblings (post-wrap in-flight policy: refuse only a still-building/pending run on THIS workspace; allow the same wrapped run), so the three guards' alignment is intentional, not incidental — this satisfies the ticket's 'one owner for the post-wrap in-flight policy' intent without over-refactoring the two working siblings.\n\nMUST NOT BREAK: support-commit and Deb-repair guards unchanged; the cross-workspace and pending-reservation protections preserved (a different workspace's running run must NOT block authoring here; a 'pending' reservation on THIS workspace must still refuse). Do not weaken the guard into a tautology.\n\nTESTS — packages/daemon/tests/authoring-play.test.ts. The existing test 'refuses while any run is in flight and commits nothing' (~L147) sets inFlight.set('cocoder', 'run_busy') with no store record; under the new logic getRun('run_busy') is undefined so it still 409s — keep it but RENAME it to reflect it pins the pending/unknown-active refusal, or better, make it pin a real RUNNING run. Then ADD two tests that pin the ticket's acceptance: (1) POST-WRAP SAME-RUN ALLOWANCE — create a run in the store on workspace 'cocoder' with status NOT 'running' (a wrapped/awaiting-founder run), set inFlight.set('cocoder', thatRunId), and assert requestAuthoringPlay returns 200 and commits (mirror the create-priority happy-path's runHeadless + assertions); (2) DIFFERENT/ACTIVE-RUN REFUSAL — set inFlight to a run with status 'running' (or the 'pending' reservation) and assert 409 with nothing committed (HEAD unchanged, headlessInputs empty). Use store.upsertRun/createRun or whatever the RunStore API exposes to seed a run with a chosen status — inspect @cocoder/core RunStore for the right method; if seeding a status is awkward, set the run then mutate status via the store's update method. Match the existing fixture/test style exactly.\n\nVERIFY BEFORE DONE: run the daemon package test suite (the authoring-play file at minimum, e.g. `pnpm --filter @cocoder/daemon test authoring-play` or the repo's vitest invocation) AND the daemon typecheck (`pnpm --filter @cocoder/daemon typecheck` or equivalent), and report the actual command + exit code + the new tests passing. Scope: packages/daemon/src/launcher.ts and packages/daemon/tests/authoring-play.test.ts only."}}
